ther at all times. Also, no crossteaming. These three hypothetical players will create simultaneously and group throughout their careers. Bear in mind that the team has to be good for xp grinds as well as a variety of PvP situations (in other words, while three rogues would be an evil PvP team, they'd be less adequate grinding Ulthorks for xp).<br>
<br>
I'm leaning toward Iksar SK, necro, and shaman.<br>
<br>
Thoughts?<br>
<br>
Argyll MacGuinness<br>
35 Rogue of the Seventh Hammer<br>
(witty sig goes here) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cylant>Cylant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/16/01 2:44:46 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 3-player PvP team</span><hr size=1> I've been thinking about this type of thing as well.<br>
-<br>
Ranger<br>
Shaman<br>
Rogue.  Possibly a bard.<br>
-<br>
Explanation:<br>
Ranger has tracking, snare, slight healing, sow, and NICE melee damage.<br>
Shaman has excellent buffs(enough to make a ranger a nice tank), nice damage, nice pet, and various other utilities.<br>
Rogue does tons of damage.<br>
Bards can provide basicly anything you need, and make sure none of you ever lose in a pvp situation.<br>
---<br>
In PvE, all three of those could group together, or any pair would work.<br>
In pvp, it would be lethal.  Buff yourself beyond beleif.  Track the victim down.  Open up with a snare, and lay into him.  Debuff him so he can't do anything.  Leave with smiles on your faces after the shaman heals you all up.  This would also work in any pair combination.<br>
--<br>
You would all need to be on the humanoid team to avoid cross teaming. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udovewhispersilk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dove Whispersilk</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/16/01 5:28:09 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 3-player PvP team</span><hr size=1> Necro, necro, druid?<br>
<br>
You gets Pets, Nukes, Snares, DoT's, SoWs and Ports.<br>
<br>
best soloing classes in the game and 2 of the best pvp classes in the game.  I know it sounds kinda boring and cheesy but if you want power that is it. <p><img src=http://ebonydragon.homestead.com/files/dove3.jpg> <BR>
Dove the Silent, rank 60 Assassin of Terris-Thule</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukambic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kambic</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.13thshadowcompany.com/svimages/new_post.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/16/01 8:03:57 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 3-player PvP team</span><hr size=1> Shaman, Rogue, Necro.<br>
<br>
Pet could tank (or you could fear kite like heck with sham + nec dots [if they stack]) by using root and prox aggro.<br>
<br>
In PvP Shaman could debuff, necro could rotissary him and snare him, rogue beats the crap out of them.<br>
<br>
SoW all the time of course, as well as haste regen and a second pet later in the shamans life.<br>
<br>
Later in the necro's life, mezmerize.<br>
<br>
Rogue, excellent damage, corpse recovery, etc. Disarm for PvP, as well as poisons (do they stack with nec/sham spells?).<br>
<br>
---<br>
<br>
3 Necs sound good as well ;p<br>
<br>
<br>
